# Build artifacts — regenerated by `go build` / `pnpm run build`.
/canopy
/canopy-*
*.test
*.exe

# Embedded UI is generated from ui/build/ by the embed-copy step.
# Source of truth is ui/src/; never check the copy in.
/internal/embed/ui/

# Local databases (ingest output, smoke-test fixtures).
*.db
*.db-journal

# Test artifacts.
/coverage.out
/profile.out

# Editor / OS.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Local environment overrides.
/.env
/.env.local

# UI workspace junk.
/ui/node_modules/
/ui/.svelte-kit/
/ui/build/

# vendor/ — TEMPORARILY COMMITTED.
#
# canopy depends on ~12 sibling libraries (assay, go-bzlmod, bigorna,
# understory, …) that aren't yet published with stable tags. go.mod
# uses relative-path `replace` directives to find them during local
# dev (`../sibling-name`), but those paths don't exist in a fresh
# clone or a stock CI checkout — `go build` would fail without
# committed vendor/. Vendoring closes the gap until the sibling libs
# ship with real versions on the module proxy.
#
# When that day comes: uncomment the line below + run
# `git rm -r --cached vendor/` + drop the `replace` directives from
# go.mod + pin the `require` lines to real versions.
#
# /vendor/

# playwright-mcp browser-session console logs. Accumulates one file
# per page interaction during UI smoke testing via the playwright-mcp
# tool. Runtime artifact, never source.
/.playwright-mcp/
